Subfloor Plumbing / Drainage to be tested prior to being backfilled and covered, pipework is to be filled to floor level for a minimum period of 30 minutes without loss in accordance with NZBC G13.7

First fix testing requirements prior to wall lining being installed. Test potable water within apartments, before linings are installed to 1,500kpa for a minimum period of 15 minutes, in accordance with Building Code NZBC G12.7.5.1a. Use appropriated pressure test equipment.
Test potable PP-R (green pipe) water supplies to a pressure of 2,000kpa in accordance with Building Code NZBC G12, and manufacturers recommendations. Use appropriated pressure test equipment
Soil waste and vent pipes are to be tested to flood level for a minimum period of 30 minutes without loss in accordance with NZBC G13.7
All testing is to be witnessed by local council authority
Hot water cylinders installed in accordance with NZBC G12 reatrained in accordance with figure 14 and thermostat set a minimum of not less than 60°C, Tempering valves to be set to 55°C maximum.
Sanitary fixtures to be installed in accordance with NZBC G13 and tested for leaks and loss of trap seal
